<section xml:id="notes-week-01">
  <title>Week 1</title>

<definition>
    <statement>
      <p>
        A <term>linear equation</term> in the variables
        <m>x_{1},x_{2},\ldots,x_{n}</m> is an equation of the form
      </p>
      <md>
        a_{1}x_{1}+a_{2}x_{2}+\cdots+a_{n}x_{n}=b,
      </md>

      <p>
        where the <m>a_{1},\ldots,a_{n}</m> and <m>b</m> are constants.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>

  <example>
     <p>
    The equation
  </p>
  <md>
    3x_{1}-2x_{2}+7x_{3}=5
  </md>
  <p>
    is linear.
  </p>
  </example>

    <p>
    A <term>system of linear equations</term> is a collection of linear
    equations involving the same variables (e.g.
    <m>x_{1}, x_{2}, \dots, x_{n}</m> ).
  </p>

  <definition>
    <statement>
      <p>
        A <term>solution</term> to a system is a choice of values for the
        variables that makes every equation in the system true.
      </p>

      <p>
        The <term>solution set</term> is the set of all solutions to a system
        of linear equations.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>

  <example>
      <p>
        The system of linear equations
      </p>
      <md>
        \begin{aligned}x+y&amp;= 5,\\ 2x-y&amp;= 1 \end{aligned}
      </md>

      <p>
        has solution <m>x=2, y=3</m> because
      </p>
      <md>
        2+3=5 \quad \textit{and}\quad 2(2)-3=1.
      </md>
      <p>
        You can see that this is the only solution by algebraically eliminating one of the variables, or by graphing the two lines and seeing that they intersect at a single point, as shown below.
      </p>

        <image width="60%">
    <shortdescription>
      Graph of the lines x plus y equals 5 and 2x minus y equals 1 intersecting at the point (2,3).
    </shortdescription>
    <latex-image>
\begin{tikzpicture}
  \draw[step=2, gray!25, thin] (-2,-2) grid (8,8);
  \draw[->, thick] (-2,0) -- (7.2,0) node[right] {$x$};
  \draw[->, thick] (0,-2) -- (0,7.1) node[above] {$y$};
  \foreach \x in {2,4,6}
    \draw (\x,0.08) -- (\x,-0.08) node[below] {\small $\x$};
  \foreach \y in {2,4,6}
    \draw (0.08,\y) -- (-0.08,\y) node[left] {\small $\y$};
  \draw[very thick, blue] (-1.5,6.5) -- (6.5,-1.5)
    node[pos=0.6, above right] {$x+y=5$};
  \draw[very thick, red] (-0.25,-1.5) -- (4.25,7.5)
    node[pos=0.8, right] {$2x-y=1$};
  \filldraw[black] (2,3) circle (3pt);
  \node[above right] at (2.25,2.75) {$(2,3)$};
\end{tikzpicture}
    </latex-image>
  </image>

  </example>



</section>
